Lorraine and her team specialize in holistic health, empowering individuals to put themselves first and take control over how they nourish their body. In today's world, it is very easy to get caught up with work obligations and deadlines. This can lead to weight gain, especially around the abdominal area caused by an increase of cortisol production. Thus further leading to an imbalance of hormones, brain fog, adrenal fatigue, obesity, insulin resistance, thyroid disease and in women, PCOS. 

At LKN, we take a compassionate and holistic approach to assist individuals to recognize the negative effects poor diet and stress can have on the body. We teach people how to make the changes necessary to improve their health by making positive dietary changes that are sustainable and become a lifestyle. We do not believe in fad diets, nor do we endorse any products or supplements. We focus on the science of food, and the principles of nutrition. We teach women how to fuel their body with real food, and optimal nutrition. Our goal is for every person to live a nourished healthy life for a healthier body and mind!

Are you looking for a fresh approach to eating? Compass Nutrition creates a trusting and supportive environment to help you maintain a healthy lifestyle. We do not believe in judgment, deprivation, punishment, guilt, and all-or-nothing rules. 

We focus on creating enjoyable habits that lead to healthy behaviors. Our approach is simple: eat what you like, learn to moderate certain foods and make informed food decisions. 

We teach our patients new skills or reinforce current skills, so that they can get to know and trust their own body cues, move away from diet rules (and rule breaking), learn better and more insight-oriented coping strategies. Our goal is to move towards a more natural, balanced, self-led style of eating and relationship with food.

During your appointment, you will find that our treatments go beyond issuing short-term meal plans. We help our patients figure out what got their eating off-track and what perceptions, attitudes, and life-style habits are contributing factors.

For some, finding that balance is merely a matter of awareness - of how to bring a fresh approach of good eating and physical activity to each day.

For others, coordinating medical nutrition therapy and daily physical activity with other health care professionals and support groups may be what is needed.

Whatever your needs are we can individually assess and design a plan that is right for you and your goals. 

Start today!

column3:
Clients come to me to heal their relationships with food and their bodies so they can live a fuller life. You may have a desire to lose weight but are beginning to understand that dieting and restriction no longer serve you. You may be unsure and nervous about how to navigate the world without food and exercise rules, but want to explore how to have a relaxed approach to eating and movement. You may want to feel less guilt and shame around eating and learn how to truly enjoy food. You may also be interested in developing skills for dealing with difficult body image days.

I believe in a weight-inclusive approach that focuses on healthy behaviors instead of restriction and weight. I provide respectful care to people of all sizes, and work to promote flexible, individualized eating. Using intuitive eating principles, I will help you end the cycle of dieting, and guide you towards a peaceful relationship with food and your body.

I provide a warm, non-judgmental environment for you to freely discuss your food and body concerns. I will never tell you what to do or judge you for any past or current behaviors or for desiring to lose weight. Together, we will explore what behaviors are helpful and harmful and you are free to keep them up or not.

I'm a Registered Dietitian Nutritionist (RD) and a Certified Dietitian Nutritionist in the state of New York. My specialities include prenatal, postnatal, pediatrics, and plant-based diets. I make it easier for moms-to-be, mothers, and their families to choose the foods that they love while also nourishing and fueling themselves. Incorporating a positive relationship with foods and your eating habits can make such a huge difference in your health (and life) and you can take control over this with the right guidance. As an RD, I only provide scientifically backed, evidence-based nutrition advice. I also rely heavily on my plant-based approach. I focus so much on plant-based foods because the research consistently indicates how beneficial having a diet full of these types of foods is. I encourage my clients to incorporate more fruits, vegetables, nuts, seeds, and whole grains while still enjoying things like pizza, chips, chocolate, and cake. I truly believe that health and happiness comes from a well-balanced diet that emphasizes plants but also leaves room for the other stuff. 

I'd love to help you on your journey towards nourishing yourself and/or your family while also having a positive relationship with food. Please contact me for your free 15 minute discovery call to see if working together will help you!

My nutritional  programs start at one  month long and can be ongoing for as much time as needed. The initial consult we will go over your medical history, dietary and exercise habits, and goals. Whether you need more energy, strength, better digestion, less stress, to sleep better or lose weight, I can get you there. I don't believe in rigidity, cutting out food groups, deprivation, or liquid diets. I want you to succeed and not feel restricted. This should be a lifestyle, not just simply about the scale or short term success. It's most important to feel healthy, confident and strong for the long-term!

Our follow up is generally once per week which can be in the office or via phone/Skype if you live out of town. I will ask you to keep a food/exercise diary online which I have access to so I can review your progress. Additionally, many of my clients are very social and eat out a lot. If that sounds like you, I can review menus from places you frequent and direct you on how to order if designing a meal plan just doesn't fit into your lifestyle. During our program, you will have unlimited access to email and text messages and will be responded to always within a timely fashion.

My job is to educate and and empower you to feel good about your food choices so you feel radiant and unstoppable- all the time.   If this sounds like something you've been waiting for let me know what you're struggling with.

Whole Body Cryotherapy
Whole Body Cryotherapy (WBC) exposes the body to sub-zero temperatures -- as low as -240 degrees -- for short periods of time (2-3 minutes), initiating various therapeutic responses within the biochemistry. As the skin responds to the rapidly cooling temperatures, it signals a chain of physiological reactions that stimulate circulation, healing and detoxification.

Gravity Colon Hydrotherapy
Gravity Colon Hydrotherapy uses the natural flow of gravity to introduce water into the body. Using the latest in water filtration technology, our custom-made treatment rooms use ultra-purified water to dissolve and carry wastes away. Our team is certified in the Woods Method of Gravity Colonics and is additionally trained in-house before joining our team. Sessions generally last 45 minutes to one hour...

Patients who require and qualify to receive homecare can obtain these services from a family member, friend, neighbor or any individual of their choice.

column1: Darling Essentials -  Lisa Kurz, MD, IBCLC
column3: Darling Essentials is a pediatrician owned and run breastfeeding medicine practice. Lisa Kurz, M.D., IBCLC began Darling Essentials in order to give women and families the proper support and education to successfully breastfeed via the help of a medical doctor.  She is a practicing pediatrician and international board certified lactation consultant who specializes in breastfeeding medicine, parenting, and nutrition.  She completed her residency at the Children's Hospital of NY at Columbia University Medical Center in 2012 and works locally as a pediatrician part-time. She is also a parent of 3 lovely children, all of whom she has breastfed with the support of her family.

Dr. Saltzman realized a calling to medicine during the height of the HIV/AIDS crisis in New York City in the mid-eighties.  Prior to entering the field of medicine Dr. Saltzman worked in the music business for record companies and publishers. Moving in the NYC club scene of the nineties, Dr. Saltzman saw many of her friends and colleagues become ill with AIDS.  She observed the rampant prejudice and stigma that LGBTQ people and IV drug users suffered, and committed herself to becoming a physician specializing in HIV/AIDS.

Despite not having a background in the sciences Dr. Saltzman was able to earn admission to medical school, while supporting herself as a single parent.  After medical school, she chose to do her residency at St. Vincent's Hospital in New York City, which was at the forefront of providing specialized treatment for patients with HIV/AIDS.  After completing her residency, she practiced at the Samuels Clinic at Roosevelt Hospital (now The Institute for Advanced Medicine at Mount Sinai), a major outpatient center for patients during the epidemic.  While practicing at the Samuels Clinic, Dr. Saltzman was an early prescriber of the "triple cocktail", the first effective combination therapy for HIV.
Dr. Saltzman's interest in addiction was born out of her experience providing care for HIV/AIDS patients who were often IV drug users...

About the Practice
Arsenio Medical, P.C., is dedicated to the prevention, diagnosis, and treatment of common medical problems for the entire family, from adolescence on up to the most senior members. The health care providers specialize in primary care and general health assessments, with an emphasis on caring for the whole person, giving patients in Lawrence, New York, peace of mind knowing that their medical needs are being expertly looked after.
As internists and family medicine practitioners, the team monitors each of their patients vigilantly, watching out for any potential problems and swiftly taking action in order to prevent complications. Whether it's a chronic illness, an acute injury, or routine care, the staff at Arsenio Medical has the tools and experience necessary to treat most medical problems.

Utilizing the diagnostic tools of Ayurveda, such as inquiry, where I go through a full range of questioning that would include your medical history, observing your physical features to glean information about your constitution, asking about when a certain imbalance (or imbalances) began and looking at how it may correlate with a certain stage of life, to even what type of dreams you have; pulse analysis, for observing how the doshas (humours) are acting on a superficial and deep level of the body & mind; and tongue analysis, which allows us to get a glimpse of what's happening with the organs.

Leo Treyzon, MD, MS is an attending physician and recent Clinical Chief of the Division of Gastroenterology at Cedars-Sinai Medical Center. He is a board certified specialist in clinical nutrition and gastroenterology. He specializes in the best treatment of irritable bowel syndrome (IBS), Crohn's and Colitis (IBD), gastro-esophageal reflux disease (GERD), ulcers (PUD), gastritis (H. Pylori), small intestinal bacterial overgrowth (SIBO), and cancers of the digestive tract. Common symptoms he treats include abdominal pain, gas, bloating, diarrhea, constipation, anemia and bleeding.
He is a participating physician and researcher in the Cedars-Sinai Weight Loss Center, Esophageal Center and Cancer Center. Dr. Treyzon performs procedures such as endoscopy, colonoscopy and wireless capsule endoscopy.
Dr. Treyzon lectures on subjects related to the field of gastroenterology, nutrition and functional abdominal pain. He is an assistant professor at the David Geffen School of Medicine at the University of California, Los Angeles (UCLA). As an educator he teaches the medical students, residents, and fellows who are training in gastroenterology. He has written many peer reviewed articles and textbook chapters on various gastrointestinal subjects.

Nutritional Balancing is a well-documented science using Hair Mineral Analysis to uncover deficiencies and imbalances within the body that create stress and symptoms.  

Symptoms are the body's way of communicating needs, and many bodily signs we take for granted could indicate much more severe problems.  For example, ridging in the nails usually indicate an iron deficiency.  But taking iron alone, will not correct the imbalance.  Its the relationship of the minerals in your body that gives you vitality.  We teach you what to look for, and how to respond to it allowing deep, permanent healing so you can go out and live a happy, healthy life.

Healthy foods provided at no cost include: Fruit, vegetables, Milk, (Cow's milk, lactose-free milk, and soy milk available), eggs, beans, peanut butter, whole grains (tortillas, pasta, oatmeal, bread, brown rice, cereals, barley and bulgur), breakfast cereal, yogurt, cheese, 100% juice, tofu, canned fish, baby food, infant cereal, and infant formula. The WIC food package will vary based on  participant age and other factors. WIC employs Registered Dietitian Nutritionists, Certified Lactation Educators, and an International Board Certified Lactation Consultants (IBCLC). column3:
In my holistic practice, I focus on stress and the underlying issues related to illness. Long-term stress challenges the body's ability to self-regulate, or heal itself naturally, and leads to disease.

My focus on Self- Regulation, as a systemic model of health and wellness, is considerably different than the Disease model, which is designed to diagnose and treat symptoms only, and often at the expense of overall systemic functioning. The Self-Regulation model considers the bigger picture and addresses the whole system, including underlying health issues that may be present. 

I use three different tools. The first is Nutritional Balancing, which is based on a Hair Mineral Analysis (HMA). This is a simple way to measure how the body is managing stress biochemically, allowing us to gain a deeper understanding of adrenal, thyroid and blood sugar functions, as well as the functionality of overall metabolism. 

The second tool I use is Biofeedback. For this, I rely on some of the most state-of-the-art technologies coming from Germany and Russia.  These technologies capture data on the energy, or information field, of the body. They then provide corrective information back to the body, in the form of biofeedback, which stimulates the body's own self-regulatory capacities and promotes proper immune function.

The third tool is Astrology, which can both assist a person on a transformational path, and reveal ways in which that person manages stress.

column3: The Renfrew Center has been the pioneer in the treatment of eating disorders since 1985. As the nation's first residential eating disorder facility, now with 19 locations throughout the country, Renfrew has helped more than 85,000 adolescent girls and women with eating disorders move towards recovery. Renfrew provides women suffering from anorexia nervosa, bulimia nervosa, binge eating disorder, and related mental health problems with the tools they need to succeed in recovery and in life. Renfrew's extensive range of services includes residential, day treatment, intensive outpatient, and outpatient programs. Each treatment level is built upon The Renfrew Center Unified Treatment Model for Eating Disorders™, an evidence-based, emotion-focused therapy that addresses eating disorders and co-morbid symptoms. Within this model, individual and group therapy are enhanced with a diverse array of services to meet patients' needs. Renfrew accepts most major insurances and is a preferred provider for all levels of treatment.

Dr. Tanya M. Reynolds, Doctor of Chiropractic Health Care; BS in Dietary Nutrition, has led her professional health care practice for over 10 years. She is currently serving patients at In8Love Chiropractic in West Los Angeles, California. She has cared for thousands of patients and has performed over 250,000 adjustments.
Dr. Tanya's passion for Chiropractic originated at the age of 15 when an MD diagnosed her with cervical dysplasia (precancerous cells of the cervix). To say the least, this was a most shocking realization. After several unsuccessful surgeries, she consulted with a Chiropractor who immediately started a series of manual manipulation, adjustments, and dietary changes.
Surprisingly after several months, she was re-tested for cancer and was cleared of the cervical dysplasia. Thankfully, additional surgery was determined unnecessary for the teenage child. Amazed by this miracle that healed her health, Dr. Tanya began studying and learning all that she could about Chiropractic.
Dr. Tanya took this passion to Life University in Marietta, Georgia. She graduated with both her BS in Dietary Nutrition, followed by a Doctorate of Chiropractic Health Care. Dedicated to spreading the word about Chiropractic, she became a Chiropractic Assistant for an office in her hometown Naples, Florida. Soon thereafter she opened her own office in January 2003.
Deciding to move her family to California, she sold her Florida practice and moved west...

The Workout Revolution specializes in slow-motion, high-intensity strength training, commonly referred to as SuperSlow®, Power of 10®, or Slow Burn®. This type of slow strength training is one of the safest, most effective, time efficient forms of exercise. The complete, total body workout lasts only 20-25 minutes and is typically done once or twice a week.

Exercise to the intensity of muscle failure (the point at which you can no longer move the weight) will thoroughly exhaust your muscle and create a stimulus to which your body must adapt. Your workouts are customized specifically for you and include nutrition suggestions (if requested) and post-exercise rest and recovery recommendations.

All sessions are private and one-on-one with one of our certified instructors using specifically designed and curated equipment. Whether you are a professional athlete, a beginner to exercise or dealing with a condition like osteoporosis, osteopenia, arthritis or chronic back pain, our science-backed method will help you build muscle, increase bone density, and enhance cardiovascular fitness while staying injury free.

Huy Quang Hoang, MD, is a native of Vietnam and graduated from the University of Maryland. He moved to southern California to study internal medicine and then acupuncture at UCLA. He has worked at prestigious hospitals such as Cedars-Sinai Medical Center in Los Angeles, and he is now medical director of Natural Health Medical Center in Lawndale, CA. 
Dr. Hoang practices conventional Western as well as natural medicine. He believes that each has its own benefits. Together, they can provide the best possible health care for many patients although he leans towards natural medicine whenever possible. He looks at the ideal role of medicine as being preventive, not curative. When the body has an ailment, Dr. Hoang applies medicine to support the body's natural healing processes. He sees total health as being not just physical, but a combination of body, mind, and spirit. His practice is centered on the patients, not their medical conditions. Dr. Hoang promises to look for the best treatment for each individual patient. In turn, he encourages patients to take responsibility for their own health.

column3:
Myodetox:
Reset your body's tension patterns with this fusion of advanced manual therapy techniques (Structural integration, neuromuscular therapy & Active Release Therapy). Myodetox is used in physical therapy to target pain, muscular imbalances and dysfunction by manipulating tissues to give improved body alignment and freedom of movement. I address the global fascial tension as well as local neuromuscular tensions, which effect movement and cause postural discrepancies.

Corrective exercise:
Specializing in Postural Restoration Institute PRI, Dynamic Neuromuscular Stabilization DNS & Functional Range Conditioning FRC to provide a service to make long-term differences to your movement, core and body mechanics. Corrective exercise targets 'local' smaller muscle groups (as opposed to 'global' larger muscles), which can often be neglected. 

Strength & Conditioning:
The key to remaining injury free and performing better is to be strong. However, current fitness trends often to overlook the areas that need to be strengthened. Redefine your body's strength and posture with training that follows up-to-date methods.

Neuro Kinetic Therpay:
Help identify muscle activation, relational compensation patterns throughout the body & how it relates to our gait cycle, breathing patterns, rotational patterns & TMJ dysfunction.

At Elite Strength Lab, our goal is to help everyone reach their unique physical and mental heights. Whether you're a young athlete looking to get a competitive edge or someone who is older with no experience with the gym, our programs will help you get to the next level--safely and effectively. Our 5 pillars to creating balanced health encompasses: movement, mobility, nutrition, recovery, and mindset. Our team uses evidence-based research and broad experiences in different fields to ensure that we are up to date with our methods. We strive to consistently grow our understanding of the human body so that we can help our clients achieve their goals and optimize their health.
 
We see clients with various goals including fat loss, building muscle, strength and conditioning for sports, improving cardiovascular health, preparation for physical testing (military, etc.), and being able to move better while being pain free. We love the diversity our clients bring because it challenges us to improve our knowledge and gives us opportunity to learn and research how to adapt to unique individuals' needs more effectively. WholeHealth Chicago is the Midwest's oldest and most respected center for integrative care, successfully blending the latest advances in conventional medicine with a wide range of clinically proven alternative therapies.   

Integrative Medicine is a growing field in which the patient and provider work together to develop a diagnostic and therapeutic program that makes sense for the individual. It combines the discipline of modern science with the wisdom of ancient healing.

This means for each patient our practitioners rely on the best evidence-based medicine and individualize a treatment plan-what we call a healing path. Your healing path might include one or more types of treatment, diagnostic testing, natural and pharmaceutical therapies, as well as referrals to other practitioners.
For people living with chronic or life-threatening illness, integrative medicine can transform life's physical, emotional, and spiritual dimensions. Integrative medicine can also be life-changing for those who are not ill but want to increase self-awareness, enhance well-being, and prevent health problems.

Please see our website for more information regarding our services and practitioners.

Neck Pain/Stiffness: can result from tension and/or muscle strain, and commonly affects regions near the neck, including the shoulder, jaw, head and upper arms. The term "stiff" neck is often used to describe the pain that results when moving your neck, especially from side-to-side. HealthSource doctors and staff effectively work to relieve your pain by freeing trapped nerves and easing stiff joints.

Carpal Tunnel:  can cause pain, as well as tingling and numbness in your hand, and stems from the buildup of pressure on the median nerve in your wrist. It can be caused by a variety of factors, including incorrectly typing on a computer keyboard, as well as pregnancy. HealthSource nerve release techniques help to erase the pain, while making sure it doesn't come back.

Sports Medicine ; includes a wide range of medical specialties, health professions and scientific disciplines, which focus on the diagnosis, treatment, and prevention of sports-related injuries.

Functional Training is the engagement in exercises that mimic or recreate everyday movement. These types of exercises typically involve the use of your full body and multiple muscle groups. This style of training builds and sculpts lean, functional muscle and all can be found at F45 Training.
 
The fixed, 45 minute duration of our workouts exists to provide a timing structure to maximize our members' growth and progress. Our daily workouts vary the amount of exercise stations, the Work Time / Rest Time ratio and the number of repetitions through the "Exercise Circuit" of each day. This provides a challenging workout for our clientele that is always evolving and never the same.
 
The motivation and encouragement in a Group Training facility create a pulsing, upbeat environment where goals are met and exceeded. Communities promoting fitness, good health and growth are forged in F45 studios around the world and are the source of our strength as an international brand.

Staying healthy is more than just about honest and simple ingredients. At Nutrasumma, it’s an entire state of mind. We live and breathe nutrition. Frankly, we’re a bit obsessed about it. We overthink it so you don’t have to.

With Nutrasumma's fermented Pea Protein powders, bacterial strains are used to make the protein powder. During the process, the peas are exposed to the bacteria, which then breaks the carbohydrates into smaller molecules so they’re easier (and faster) for the body to digest. Most of the carbohydrate molecules are then removed, making the resulting powder high in protein.

I am a hi-tech mobile clinic providing body composition analysis through hydrostatic weighing. Body Fat Test is the Gold Standard of body fat testing. Getting tested in our hydrostatic tank is a great way to establish a baseline, instrumental in creating fitness goals, or seeing the results you've made already! Testing takes just about 15 minutes, and afterward, you will receive a detailed report that includes: 

1. Your body fat and lean body mass, as percentages and in actual weight.

2. How much fat, if any, you need to lose in order to achieve your desired body composition.

3. Your Resting Metabolic Rate (RMR), unique to you (how many calories the body burns daily at rest.)

4. Your specific calorie expenditure while performing exercise. 

5. Calculation of your TDEE (total daily energy expenditure) on workout vs. non workout days.

6. How to track your calories and healthy caloric intakes/deficits based on goals.

7. Your Macros based on your calorie intake and specific goals. 

8. A reference table showing where your results rank you amongst your age and gender.

9. Detailed tracking of your history, helping benchmark progress.

10. A personalized action plan to achieve desired composition!

Resilience is a word that has become a way of life for me.  Having gone through a great deal of change and adversity in my life, I went into this line of work because I am deeply committed to taking the lessons I have learned and drawing from my wounds to give back.  I am here to guide people to realizing their full potential through harnessing resilience.

Roadmap To Resilience:  A 6 pillar approach to creating self efficacy in times of adversity.  In other words learning how to bounce back when things get tough.  Through Radical Self Care, Reclaiming Your Identity, Unconditional Acceptance, Heart Healing, Connection and Community, and Joy as a Spiritual and Daily Practice, you will harness and cultivate the skill of resilience.

In addition to coaching services I provide private, small group, and corporate yoga classes.  I also do special events like bridal showers, day of wedding parties, bachelorette parties and more.

My specialty is working one on one. I built a luxurious facility to cater to one person at a time. 

My focus is perfect execution, to feel every muscle while executing proper form. You can feel your body building muscle and burning fat. I encourage mental disciplines and techniques required to push yourself. While training, I discuss why we are doing that specific exercise and how it's going to help you reach your goal. I help you maintain a calm, centered state. Serenity in chaos, I like to call it. Working out and pushing you can and SHOULD be fun for everyone. Attitude and how you view the act of exertion is key to being successful in the gym. We will find the fun in this. 

I put a great deal of research over the years to use the most effective and safe exercises to get you the fastest results. 

We achieve your goals by using a variety of a equipment. Each piece of equipment is a mini parallel but mastery of each is a very large, rewarding accomplishment and becomes a new tool in getting you a more functional dream body.

Furthermore, we will integrate yoga, foam rolling, and other soft tissue methods to help you eliminate any muscular pain or discomfort; leaving you feeling refreshed and vibrant. 

When I'm done with you, you can walk into a gym and navigate to any piece of equipment and train at a high level

I put a lot of thought into the fun factor, what exercises you enjoy and I do my best everyday to be fun and effective.

column3: Tina is a registered dietitian nutritionist and her expertise lies in eating disorders and medical nutrition therapy for a variety of health conditions and also as a certified personal trainer through NASM. Working in the eating disorder field for over 8 years, Tina's vast experience includes various outpatient practices, but also working in both the PHP/IOP level of care.  Tina focuses on bettering her client's health and mind by employing a non-diet approach to meal planning, using intuitive and conscious eating principles.   She excels at creating personalized plans of action as well as assisting clients to incorporate nutrition and activity into their lifestyles, all done in a balanced and enjoyable way.  Tina's spunky personality can add fun and excitement when talking about nutrition, especially when de-bunking some of those challenging diet myths.   Tina always finds ways to incorporate her own enjoyment for food, cooking, and exploring new meals into her client's sessions.  She believes that exposure is a great tool in learning how to challenge food fears and the "diet mentality".  This may include grocery store and restaurant outings, or clients bringing their own meal or snack to eat with Tina during session.

Adult Substance Abuse Subtle Screening Inventory - 4 (SASSI-4)

SASSI-4 identifies high or low probability of substance use disorders and includes a prescription drug scale that identifies individuals likely to be abusing prescription medications. It also provides a measure of profile validity and clinical insight into level of defensiveness and willingness to acknowledge experienced consequences of substance use disorder.

I specialize in environmental medicine which is an emerging subset of medical specialities that looks to the environment for causative factors in changing an individuals physiology and epigenetics to cause disease. Environmental exposure includes pesticides, pharmaceuticals, chemicals, car exhaust, mold, infectious agents such as bacteria that cause Lyme as well as other infectious agents such as unusual parasites. 
I particularly specialize in detoxification and digestive diseases and have particularly refined my skill set to address healing the body from chemical exposures. I can do lab test to find out which chemicals (and infectious agents) your body may contain as well as to identify food allergies and sensitivities.
